@node SEC_A
@title "Section A :- Introduction"
@{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

@{i}Sound Palette@{ui} is a versatile librarian program for the Korg 05R/W
synthesizer. It allows a huge number of sounds to be stored in a convenient
way on your computer, so that you can arrange them into appropriate banks to
suit your needs.

@{b}Features:@{ub}

          @{b}o@{ub}    Presets can be stored in a heirarchic structure.
                (rather like a directory structure}

          @{b}o@{ub}    Descriptions can be given to each preset.

          @{b}o@{ub}    Sounds can be auditioned using a selection of tunes.

          @{b}o@{ub}    MIDI can be disabled, allowing this program to multi-task
               with other MIDI applications.

          @{b}o@{ub}    New @{i}auditioning@{ui} tunes can also be added.

          @{b}o@{ub}    A ready made database of presets comes with this software.

          @{b}o@{ub}    A single preset can be have more than one entry in
               the database without any extra disk space being taken up.
               {e.g. you may have a sound @{i}OrganPiano@{ui} and wish
               to place it in both @{i}organ@{ui} and @{i}piano@{ui} categories.)

          @{b}o@{ub}    Banks of presets can be loaded and saved in
               system exclusive format.
@endnode

@node SEC_B
@title "Section B :- Requirements"
@{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

The hardware requirements are pretty straightforward:

            A Korg 05R/W synthesizer. (Although this program @{i}may@{ui} also
            work with the X5 and 05DR synthesizers)

            A MIDI interface or PC I/F lead.

            A hard disk is recommended.

            If you have a low resolution screen, and/or a large font, this software
            will not load, as there won't be enough space for the window. It works
            fine (among other configurations) on a standard 640*256 PAL screen using
            an 8 point topaz font. With a screen mode less than 256 pixels high, the
            software will attempt to open a smaller, less attractive window.
@endnode

@node SEC_C
@title "Section C :- Installation"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

To install this software an installer script is provided. Just double-click
on its icon. No assigns or anything like that are neccessary.

The only other thing you will need to do, is make sure RTS/CTS handshaking
@{b}is not@{ub} enabled in serial preferences. The other serial settings
will not affect this software.

Both the MIDI In, and MIDI Out ports of your Korg synthesiser must be connected
to your Amiga MIDI interface for this software to work correctly.

@endnode

@node SEC_D
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Useage@{uu}@{ub}

Before running the software make sure your MIDI setup is connected correctly
and the 05R/W switched on.

            @{" General Useage " link USEAGE}
            @{" Window description " link DES_WIN}
            @{" Menu descriptions " link DES_MENU}

@endnode


