@node USE_MOVEDB
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Moving around the database@{uu}@{ub}


This is very easy. The database is shown in the left-hand list-view.
Preset entries, i.e. the sounds themselves, are shown by name.
SubLists, i.e. categories containing presets or further categories,
are prefixed by a @{b}->@{ub}.

By clicking on a preset entry, the details for the preset will be shown
below the left-hand list-view. You can then audition the preset, or copy
it to the 05R/W among other things.

By clicking on a SubList, you are taken into the SubList, and a new list
of items will appear in the list-view. The first item will be @{b}<-Back@{ub},
and by clicking on this, you can go back to the previous (or parent) list.

@endnode
   


@node USE_NEW
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Creating a new database preset entry@{uu}@{ub}


It is only necessary to do this, if you have already copied a preset from
the 05R/W to the database, and wish the same preset to appear somewhere else
in the database.

I.e. You may have made a SubList called Pianos to contain all the piano
presets, and another SubList called Organs to hold all the organ presets.
There may be a sound called OrganPiano on the 05R/W which would suit both
categories. The preset may have originally been copied to the Pianos SubList.
Using this function, you could create a new entry in the Organs SubList, and
assign it to the OrganPiano file stored on disk.

Creating a new preset entry is accomplished by pressing the @{b}New @{ub}button.
This will create an entry with the name @{b}<blank>@{ub} in the left-hand
list-view. A more suitable name can be easily given, by typing the new name
in to the @{b}Current@{ub} box in the left hand side of the window.

To assign this new entry to a preset file, click on the @{b}? @{ub}button, and
a file requester will appear from which you can select one. Alternatively, if
you know the path of the preset file, you can type it directly into the
@{b}Path @{ub}box.

If you wish to give the sound a descriptive comment, enter a comment of up to
25 characters in the @{b}Current @{ub}box.

@endnode


@node USE_NEWSUB
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Creating a new SubList@{uu}@{ub}


The SubList feature is provided to help you organise the presets of your 05R/W
in a more practical and efficient way. They allow you to categorise presets
according to what kind of sound they are. SubLists can also be created within
other SubLists.

I.e. You could have one SubList for all the string presets you have, another for
all the techno sounds etc. etc.

A new sublist is created by clicking on the @{b}New SubList@{ub} button. A new
sublist title will appear. It will initially be called @{b}<blank>@{ub}, but
you can change this to a more appropriate name, by entering the new name in the
@{b}Current @{ub}box in the left hand side of the window.

@endnode


@node USE_DELETE
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Deleting an entry from the database@{uu}@{ub}


By pressing the @{b}Delete @{ub}button you can delete either a single
preset entry from the database, or an entire SubList and any
preset/SubList entries which may be contained inside it.

The currently selected entry in the left-hand list-view is deleted. @{b}To select
a sublist@{ub}, first click on it to go into it, then click on @{b}<-Back@{ub} to
go back to the parent. The name of the SubList will now appear in the
@{b}Current@{ub} box.

When you delete a preset entry, the file associated with it on disk is
also deleted to save storeage. However, if the @{b} Search before deleting@{ub}
option is enabled in the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}, the software will search
the database to check whether any other preset entries use the same preset
file. If one or more are, you have the option of not deleting the file
associated with the preset.

When you delete an entire SubList, no such search is done - so be careful!
If anyone wants this feature, let me know and I will implement it in the next
version - I just considered it unnecessary.

@endnode


@node USE_DBAUD
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Auditioning a database preset@{uu}@{ub}


To see what a database preset sounds like before copying it to the memory of
the 05R/W, you can audition it by pressing one of the @{b}Tune @{ub}buttons in
the left hand side of the window.

What happens, is the currently selected database preset is temporarily copied
to the 05R/W. The tune is then played, and the 05R/W reverts back to whatever
preset was in it previously.   

The tune played, depends on what tune you have assigned to the button using
the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}. Each tune exists as a file on disk, which makes it
possible to have many tunes on disk for you to choose from!

The tempo the tunes are played at can also be changed using the @{"program preferences" link USE_PREFS}.

@endnode


@node USE_SORT
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Sorting the current SubList@{uu}@{ub}


To make it easier to locate a preset entry in a long list of them, the list can
be sorted. This is done by selecting @{b}Sort@{ub} from the @{b}Database Menu@{ub}.

Unless you save the database, the sort won't be made permanent. This is done by
selecting @{b}Save@{ub} from the @{" Project Menu " link MENU_PROJECT}.

@endnode


@node USE_AUD
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Auditioning a preset in the 05R/W's memory@{uu}@{ub}


This feature allows you to see what a sound in the memory of the 05R/W sounds
like before copying it to the database.

When you press one of the @{b}Tune @{ub}buttons in the right hand side of the
window, a tune will be played using the currently selected preset in the
right-hand list-view.

The tune played, depends on what tune you have assigned to the button using
the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}. Each tune exists as a file on disk, which makes it
possible to have many tunes on disk for you to choose from!

The tempo the tunes are played at can also be changed using the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}.

@endnode


@node USE_GRAB
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Grabbing the current contents of the 05R/W's memory@{uu}@{ub}


Under normal circumstances it will not be necessary to do this, as the software
does it automatically once loaded. If however you edit some of the program
presets in the 05R/W, and want the software to recognise the changes, press the
@{b}Grab @{ub}button.
@endnode


@node USE_SAVEBANK
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Saving an entire bank to disk@{uu}@{ub}


This feature allows you to save an entire bank of sounds to disk. It saves all
100 of the A-Bank sounds currently in the memory of the 05R/W as a file on disk
in system exclusive format.

The fact that they are stored in system exclusive format, means you can easily
exchange them with other 05R/W users, and upload them to Korg FTP sites etc..

It also means you can copy the bank directly to the 05R/W from AmigaDOS. In order
to do this your serial port preferences must be set up correctly:

    Baud Rate -  31250    \
    No Parity             |---- N.B. these @{b}do not@{ub} have to be set for this
    8 Bits/Char           |     software, only for copying banks using AmigaDOS.
    1 Stop Bit            /
    No HandShaking

@endnode


@node USE_LOADBANK
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Loading a new bank of sounds from disk@{uu}@{ub}


This function allows you to load a file containing an entire bank of program presets.
This could either be a bank you have previously made and saved using this software,
or one you have downloaded or obtained from another 05R/W user.

The bank must be in 05R/W system exclusive format, and only contain program presets.
I.e. if it contains combinations, drums, or multi-setup data, the software will
reject it.

@endnode


@node USE_COPYTODB
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Copying a preset from the 05R/W to the database@{uu}@{ub}


To copy a preset from the A-Bank of the 05R/W to the current database SubList,
select the preset in the 05R/W you wish to copy, by clicking on it in the
right-hand list-view, and then press the @{b}<-- @{ub}button.

A file requester will appear for you to choose where the preset file will
be stored on disk. A suitable name will be given for the file in the requester,
but you can change it if you like. The default directory that appears in this
requester can be changed using the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}.

After you have pressed OK on the file requester, the preset will be added to
the database.

This new addition to the database will only be made permanent, after the database
has been saved by selecting @{b}Save@{ub} from the @{" Project Menu " link MENU_PROJECT}.

@endnode


@node USE_COPYTORW
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Copying a preset from database to the 05R/W@{uu}@{ub}

 
To copy a preset held in the database to the A-Bank of the 05R/W, first select
the database preset to copy, by clicking on it in the left-hand list-view.
Next, select the preset in the 05R/W which is to be replaced by the database
preset, by clicking on it in the right-hand list-view.

Now press the @{b}--> @{ub}button, and the sound will be transfered to the 05R/W.

@endnode



@node USE_MIDI
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Enabling/Disabling MIDI@{uu}@{ub}

MIDI is enabled by setting the toggle button in the top-right hand corner of the
window to its pushed state.

MIDI is disabled by setting the above button to its raised state.

@endnode



@node DES_WIN
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Window description@{uu}@{ub}

Please select the area of the program window you want information on:

            @{" Lefthand side  " link DES_LEFT}
            @{" Central Column " link DES_CENTRE}
            @{" Righthand side " link DES_RIGHT}

@endnode

@node DES_LEFT
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Lefthand side of window@{uu}@{ub}


This side of the window is used to deal with the database of presets
stored on the computer.

@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}The List View@{ub} displays the contents of the database.
The entries in the list-view are either the presets themselves, or
SubLists containing presets or further SubLists.
Think of SubLists like AmigaDOS drawers.

SubLists are prefixed by a @{b}->@{ub} symbol, clicking on one will
take you into that SubList.

If you enter a SubList, the first entry in the list-view will be @{b}<- Back@{ub}.
This will take you back to the parent SubList.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Current'@{ub} shows the name of the currently selected preset or SubList.
This name is independant of the preset name displayed on the screen
of the 05R/W.
The name of the currently selected preset or sublist can be altered by
changing the contents of the box.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Comment'@{ub} shows an optional descriptive comment which can be
given to a preset. The reason for this, is that if you end up with hundreds
of presets in the database, you will most probably forget what each one
sounds like!
Comments can be added or changed by changing the contents of the box.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu} 

@{b}'Path'@{ub} - By pressing the @{b}? @{ub}button, you can change the path
that leads to the actual preset itself on your hard-disk / floppy-disk.
The current path will be shown in the text box.
You can also change the path by typing it directly into this box.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Audition'@{ub} - The @{" Tune " link USE_DBAUD} buttons here allow you to test out
the currently selected preset in the database, by using it to play a short
tune. The tune played depends on which tune has been assigned to the button
using the @{" program preferences " link USE_PREFS}.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Entry'@{ub} - This section allows you to manage the database.

The @{b}New@{ub} button creates a @{"new entry" link USE_NEW} for a preset in the database.

The @{b}New SubList@{ub} button creates a @{"new category" link USE_NEWSUB} for the presets to be stored
under.

The @{b}Delete@{ub} button @{"deletes" link USE_DELETE} whatever database entry is currently selected,
regardless of whether it is a preset or SubList.

@endnode


@node DES_CENTRE
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Central column of window@{uu}@{ub}


The buttons in this section of the window are used to transfer sounds between the
05R/W and the database.

@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
 
The @{" --> Button " link USE_COPYTORW} is used to copy a preset from the database, to whatever
preset location in the 05R/W is currently selected in the right-hand list-view.

The @{" <-- Button " link USE_COPYTODB} does the opposite. It copies whatever preset is
selected in the right-hand list-view, from the 05R/W to the database. In doing
so, it creates a new entry in the database with a suitable name, and saves the
preset to disk.

@endnode


@node DES_RIGHT
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Right hand side of window@{uu}@{ub}


This side of the window is used to deal with the sounds currently in the
memory of the 05R/W.

@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

The @{" MIDI Enabled " link USE_MIDI} button indicates and determines whether MIDI
is currently enabled or disabled.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

The @{b}List View@{ub} shows a list of all the presets already in the 05R/W.
Clicking on any preset in this list-view, will have the effect of setting
the synthesiser to this preset (like a program change).
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Current'@{ub} shows the currently selected preset from the list-view.
This will be the one copied to the database if the @{b}<--@{ub} button is pressed.
It will also be the preset in the 05R/W that is overwritten with a new one
if the @{b}-->@{ub} button is pressed.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Audition'@{ub} - The @{" Tune " link USE_AUD} buttons here are used in a similar way to the
ones in the left hand side of the window.
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

@{b}'Korg Memory'@{ub} - The @{" Grab " link USE_GRAB} will receive all the A-Bank sounds
currently in the 05R/W. This is done automatically after the program has
loaded, but is there incase for example you alter any sounds using the
05R/W itself.

@endnode


@node DES_MENU
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Menu descriptions@{uu}@{ub}


Please select the menu you want more information on:

            @{" Project " link MENU_PROJECT}
            @{" Database " link MENU_DATABASE}
            @{" Bank " link MENU_BANK}

@endnode

@node MENU_PROJECT
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Project Menu@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}About@{ub} - Displays the loading logo of this software.

@{b}Save@{ub} - Saves the database of presets.

@{b}Preferences@{ub} - Brings up the @{" preferences " link USE_PREFS} window.

@{b}Quit@{ub} - Exits the software.

@endnode


@node MENU_DATABASE
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Database Menu@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Sort@{ub} - Alphabetically sorts the current database sublist.

@endnode

@node MENU_BANK
@title "Section D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Bank Menu@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Load@{ub} - Loads an entire bank of sounds from disk, and sends them to the 05R/W.

                The banks must be in system exclusive format, and
                contain only program presets, i.e. not combinations etc.

@{b}Save@{ub} - Saves the current bank of sounds in the 05R/W to disk.
                They are saved in system exclusive form.

@endnode


@node USE_PREFS
@title "Sectionn D :- Useage"
@{b}@{u}Setting the program preferences@{uu}@{ub}


The program preferences are set by choosing @{b}Preferences@{ub} from the
@{" Project Menu " link MENU_PROJECT}. The preferences window will then open.

@{b}Graphic Requesters@{ub} - If enabled, any program requesters that appears will
have a pretty icon in. The option to disable this feature is there for floppy users,
to improve the speed of loading.

@{b}Show about at startup@{ub} - @{b}This feature only affects registered users@{ub}.
If disabled, the About requester is not shown when the program is loaded.

@{b}Search before deleting@{ub} - If enabled, whenever you delete a preset entry from
the database, a search is done to see if any other database presets use the same file.
If so, you are warned, and given the option to not delete the preset file from disk.

@{b}Audition Tempo@{ub} - This is the tempo (in BPM) the audition tunes will be played at.
The maximum is currently set at 255.

@{b}Presets Path@{ub} - This is the default path this software tries to save preset files
to when you transfer them from the 05R/W to the database.

@{b}Tune Paths@{ub} - The three tune path buttons and boxes, are used to hold the name
and path of the audition tune to be assigned to each button. The filenames of audition
tunes usually end with @{b}.aud@{ub}, and several come with this software - try loading them!

@endnode

@node SEC_EE
@title "Section E :- The Audition program"
@{b}@{u}Audition - A program to write your own auditioning tunes@{uu}@{ub}


Firstly, this program is not user friendly. I only wrote it for my own use,
but included it with this software incase anyone was brave enough to use it.
It requires a little knowledge as to how notes are played through MIDI.

It allows you to write tunes to be used to test the presets held in the
librarian.

Before using it, sketch out your tune on paper so that you know how long each
note will be.

It is used as follows:

    Run it from the cli:   Audition <filename>

    You will then get a prompt asking you for a command.

    Type @{b}1@{ub} for a note on.
         @{b}2@{ub} for a note off.
         @{b}3@{ub} for a rest (place between a note on and note off
                                         to give a note duration)
         @{b}4@{ub} to finish


    @{b}Note On@{ub}

    You are asked for the 05R/W channel the note is to be played on.
    Use 0 for the purposes of this software.

    You are then asked for the note. Type in the MIDI note number.
    (MIDI note numbers are shown in your 05R/W Voice Name List booklet).

    Lastly, you are asked for the velocity. This can be from 0  - softest
                                                             64 - loudest

    @{b}Note Off@{ub}

    You are asked for the 05R/W channel of the note to turn off.
    Use the same channel you used for the note on of that note.
    You are then asked for the note number. Use the same number you used
    to turn the note on.


    @{b}Rest@{ub}

    Use this to give a note duration by placing it between note on and
    note off commands. It can also be used as a rest, to provide a gap
    in the tune.
    You are asked for the duration. This must be given in the number of
    semi-quavers the rest is for.

    I.e. for a:   semi-quaver type 1
                       quaver type 2
                     crotchet type 4
                        minim type 8 etc.


    @{b}Any mistakes made cannot be corrected, you'll have to start again
    from scratch.@{ub}

    I may program a more user-friendly version of this in future.
@endnode


@node SEC_E
@title "Section F :- Demo Limitations"
@{b}@{u}Limitations on the Unregistered Version@{uu}@{ub}


There are only 2 restrictions:

        1)  You can only hold a maximum of 60 presets in the database.
            (With the registered version there is no limit!)

        2)  You can't disable the About requester popping up when the program loads.


For further information about registering (It doesn't cost much!) see @{" Registering " link SEC_F}.

@endnode


@node SEC_F
@title "Section G :- Registering"
@{b}@{u}Becoming a registered user@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Why register?@{ub}

Well :- 1) You can store as many presets as you like in the database.

        2) You'll get a pre-made database with @{b}loads@{ub} of presets in.
           (not just 50)

        3) You'll get more tunes to audition the presets with.

        4) You'll get free updates, unless a major new version is released.

        5) You'll get a reduction on the price of registering to my Patch Editor
           program when I've finished it. It will be a lot better than any others
           currently available on the Amiga!

        6) It's taken me ages to write, it'll be nice to see who's using it, and get
           a bit of cash back in return for my efforts!


@{b}Here's How@{ub}

        @{b}The Price:@{ub}          Through E-Mail               - 10 English Pounds.
                            Through the post (UK)        - 11 English Pounds
                            Through the post (Elsewhere) - 12 English Pounds

        @{b}Method of payment:@{ub}  Cash if you live outside the UK,
                            otherwise a cheque will do.

        @{b}Send payment to:@{ub}    James Hollingsworth,
                            31 Long Gore,
                            Farncombe,
                            Surrey,
                            GU7 3TE,
                            ENGLAND.

        Although you may think sending cash through the post is risky, I've done it several
        times, and never had any trouble! I advise taping any coins to a piece of card.
        Don't forget to include your postal address and E-Mail address if you have one.

        Once I've received payment, I'll post or E-Mail you the keyfile, with details on how
        to use it, along with the database, and further audition tunes.

        Any queries, just write, phone  :- 01483 422845
                              or E-Mail :- SoundPalette@spiders.demon.co.uk

@endnode



@node SEC_G
@title "Section H :- Future"
@{b}@{u}Plans for future versions of this software@{uu}@{ub}


This will partly depend on the ideas put forward by you and other users, but
possible ideas I have are:

        1) The ability to have several databases, maybe with more than one loaded at once.

        2) I may possibly get this software to use the midi.library, so that other
           programs which use it can run at the same time.

        3) In the mean time, I'm going to write an 05R/W commodity which will have a GUI
           the same as the front panel of the synthesiser, allowing you to control it easily
           from the Amiga. This, and any other software I write for the 05R/W, will then all
           run through it simultaneously.

        4) A more user friendly Audition program for writing your own tunes.

        5) Search functions to search the list of presets in the 05R/W for ones containing a
           keyword such as 'Piano', and then add all the found presets to the database at once.

        6) Improved deletion of database presets. At the moment when you delete one, a search
           can be done to see if any other database presets use the same preset file, but no
           facility exists to let you remove those database presets also.

        7) Possibly a search feature to search the database for a specific preset.

        8) Possibly an even nicer GUI!

Any suggestions of your own, just write or E-Mail me, the addresses are @{" here " link SEC_F}.
@endnode


